  1→//axhob_operation
  2→{rbtgo_director_create}
  3→
  4→The
  5→{rbtr_governor}
  6→creates a
  7→{rbtr_director}
  8→{giam_service_account}
  9→with build management permissions:
 10→
 11→//axhoq_precondition
 12→* Execute {rbtoe_check_rubric_repo_url} (validates {rbrr_rubric_repo_url} using PAT from Secret Manager)
 13→
 14→//axhoq_precondition
 15→* Execute {rbtoe_check_cbv2_connection} to verify {rbtgi_cbv2_connection} is active
 16→
 17→//axhop_parameter_from_type
 18→{rbtr_director}
 19→. *Validate Input Parameters*:
 20→.. {rbbc_require}
 21→`«INPUT_INSTANCE»` provided as first argument
 22→.. {rbbc_store}
 23→`«DIRECTOR_ACCOUNT_NAME»` as `director-«INPUT_INSTANCE»`
 24→.. {rbbc_store}
 25→`«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` as `«DIRECTOR_ACCOUNT_NAME»@{rbrr_depot_project_id}.iam.gserviceaccount.com`
 26→
 27→//axhoq_precondition
 28→* {rbbc_require}
 29→`BURD_OUTPUT_DIR` environment variable set and directory exists
 30→
 31→//axhos_step
 32→. *Authenticate as
 33→{rbtr_governor}*:
 34→.. Execute
 35→{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
 36→.. {rbbc_store}
 37→`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls
 38→
 39→//axhos_step
 40→. *Create
 41→{rbtr_director}
 42→Service Account*:
 43→.. {rbbc_call}
 44→link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/create[iam.serviceAccounts.create] with:
 45→... accountId: `«DIRECTOR_ACCOUNT_NAME»`
 46→... displayName: `Recipe Bottle Director («INPUT_INSTANCE»)`
 47→... description: `Create/destroy container images for «INPUT_INSTANCE»`
 48→... project:
 49→{rbrr_depot_project_id}
 50→.. {rbbc_require}
 51→HTTP 200 response
 52→.. {rbbc_store}
 53→`«DIRECTOR_UNIQUE_ID»` from response `.uniqueId` field
 54→
 55→//axhos_step
 56→. *Verify Service Account Propagation*:
 57→.. {rbbc_call}
 58→link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/get[iam.serviceAccounts.get] for `projects/-/serviceAccounts/«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»`
 59→.. {rbbc_poll}
 60→with backoff until HTTP 200 (newly-created SA may not be immediately resolvable by email)
 61→.. NOTE: Poll must use the email address, not the numeric ID. The email-based lookup path has independent propagation from the UID-based path, and subsequent steps (keys.list, keys.create) all use the email address. Polling by UID can succeed while the email path still returns 404.
 62→.. {rbbc_require}
 63→service account accessible by email
 64→
 65→//axhos_step
 66→. *Preflight: Ensure Pristine Key State*:
 67→.. {rbbc_call}
 68→link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts.keys/list[serviceAccounts.keys.list] for `«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»`
 69→.. {rbbc_store}
 70→`«EXISTING_KEYS»` from response `.keys[]`
 71→.. {rbbc_require}
 72→no keys with `keyType: USER_MANAGED` exist
 73→.. {rbbc_fatal}
 74→if USER_MANAGED keys found: "Manual cleanup required via Console"
 75→
 76→//axhos_step
 77→. *Generate Service Account Key*:
 78→.. {rbbc_call}
 79→link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts.keys/create[serviceAccounts.keys.create] for `«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with:
 80→... privateKeyType: `TYPE_GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS_FILE`
 81→.. {rbbc_store}
 82→`«DIRECTOR_PRIVATE_KEY_DATA»` from response `.privateKeyData` field
 83→.. {rbtoe_rbra_generate}
 84→converts `«DIRECTOR_PRIVATE_KEY_DATA»` to `«DIRECTOR_RBRA_FILE»`
 85→
 86→//axhos_step
 87→. *Get Depot Project Number*:
 88→.. {rbbc_call}
 89→link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/get[projects.get] for
 90→{rbrr_depot_project_id}
 91→.. {rbbc_store}
 92→`«PROJECT_NUMBER»` from `.projectNumber` field
 93→
 94→//axhos_step
 95→. *Grant Project-Level Permissions*:
 96→.. {rbbc_call}
 97→link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/setIamPolicy[projects.setIamPolicy] for
 98→{rbrr_depot_project_id}
 99→.. Add `serviceAccount:«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with roles:
100→... `roles/cloudbuild.builds.editor` (submit and manage builds)
101→... `roles/viewer` (read project resources)
102→.. Policy version: 3
103→.. {rbbc_require}
104→IAM policy update successful
105→
106→//axhos_step
107→. *Grant Secret Manager Access for Inscribe*:
108→.. NOTE:
109→{rbtr_director}
110→needs to fetch the API token from Secret Manager during
111→{rbtgo_rubric_inscribe}
112→to construct authenticated git URLs.
113→.. {rbbc_call}
114→link:https://cloud.google.com/secret-manager/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.secrets/getIamPolicy[secrets.getIamPolicy] for `projects/{rbrr_depot_project_id}/secrets/RBGC_CBV2_API_TOKEN_SECRET_NAME`
115→.. {rbbc_require}
116→HTTP 200 — existing policy must be read successfully before modification. Die on failure; a silent fallback to empty policy would destroy existing bindings (e.g., the Cloud Build service agent binding set by {rbtgo_depot_create}).
117→.. *Complete policy write*: Add ALL expected `secretAccessor` bindings to the read policy, regardless of what the read returned:
118→... `serviceAccount:«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` — Director needs secret access for inscribe
119→... `serviceAccount:service-«PROJECT_NUMBER»@gcp-sa-cloudbuild.iam.gserviceaccount.com` — Cloud Build service agent needs secret access at build time
120→.. NOTE: This complete-policy-write pattern prevents the IAM eventual consistency race: if `getIamPolicy` returns stale data missing the CB service agent binding (set by {rbtgo_depot_create}), the `setIamPolicy` still includes it.
121→.. {rbbc_call}
122→link:https://cloud.google.com/secret-manager/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.secrets/setIamPolicy[secrets.setIamPolicy] with the complete expected policy
123→.. {rbbc_require}
124→IAM policy set with all expected secretAccessor bindings
125→
126→//axhos_step
127→. *Grant
128→{rbtr_mason}
129→Impersonation*:
130→.. NOTE:
131→{rbtr_director}
132→submits builds that execute as
133→{rbtr_mason}.
134→This requires `serviceAccountUser` permission on
135→{rbtr_mason}.
136→.. {rbbc_call}
137→link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/setIamPolicy[serviceAccounts.setIamPolicy] for
138→{rbtr_mason}
139→service account
140→.. Add `serviceAccount:«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with `roles/iam.serviceAccountUser`
141→.. {rbbc_require}
142→IAM binding successful
143→
144→//axhos_step
145→. *Grant
146→{rbtgi_build_bucket}
147→Access*:
148→.. {rbbc_call}
149→link:https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/json_api/v1/buckets/setIamPolicy[buckets.setIamPolicy] for
150→{rbtgi_build_bucket}
151→.. Add `serviceAccount:«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with roles:
152→... `roles/storage.objectCreator` (upload sources)
153→... `roles/storage.objectViewer` (verify uploads)
154→.. {rbbc_require}
155→bucket IAM update successful
156→
157→//axhos_step
158→. *Grant
159→{rbtgi_repository}
160→Admin Access*:
161→.. {rbbc_call}
162→link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories/setIamPolicy[repositories.setIamPolicy] for
163→{rbtgi_repository}
164→.. *Complete policy write*: Add ALL expected bindings to the read policy, regardless of what the read returned:
165→... `serviceAccount:«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with `roles/artifactregistry.repoAdmin` — Director manages images
166→... `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/artifactregistry.writer` — Mason pushes images at build time
167→.. NOTE: Same complete-policy-write pattern as the secret IAM step. Prevents stale read from overwriting Mason's writer binding set by {rbtgo_depot_create}.
168→.. {rbbc_require}
169→repository IAM set with all expected bindings
170→
171→//axhoo_output_of_type
172→{rbtgi_rbra_file}
173→. *Display Installation Instructions*:
174→.. {rbbc_show}
175→Director created successfully
176→.. {rbbc_show}
177→RBRA file location: `«DIRECTOR_RBRA_FILE»`
178→.. {rbbc_show}
179→installation command:
180→... `cp "«DIRECTOR_RBRA_FILE»" "{rbrr_director_rbra_file}"`
181→.. {rbbc_warn}
182→if
183→{rbrr_director_rbra_file}
184→already exists
185→
186→//axhoc_completion
187→Successful execution creates director service account.
188→
